---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Use Cases | BeaconGuard Assurance">
  <section>
    <h1>Use Cases</h1>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard is positioned first for regulated financial workflows where probabilistic model behavior cannot act as the authorization boundary.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>High-trust Use Cases</h2>
    <div class="section-grid">
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>AI-assisted payment disputes</h3>
        <p>Request scope, case context, and action eligibility are policy-gated before any payout, reversal, or account action can proceed.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Exception operations</h3>
        <p>AI can summarize or recommend outcomes, but execution rights remain deterministic and are controlled by policy before completion.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Internal servicing workflows</h3>
        <p>Analyst and servicing flows with regulated data access and action paths are bound by explicit, reviewable controls and policy checks.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Operational Patterns</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>AI-assisted payment handling where request context and requested action must pass explicit policy checks.</li>
      <li>Exception routing where AI suggests next steps but deterministic policy controls authorize execution.</li>
      <li>Internal analyst workflows where regulated data movement and privileged actions remain policy governed and auditable.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Financial workflow focus</h2>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard is built around financial workflow governance first, where model outputs are helpful, but deterministic control is required for authorization decisions and downstream enforcement.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Explore by outcome</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/platform">Understand platform coverage</a></li>
      <li><a href="/trust-assurance">Review assurance model</a></li>
      <li><a href="/deployment">Compare deployment posture</a></li>
    </ul>
    <div class="page-actions">
      <a class="btn-primary" href="/design-partner-program">Request governance review support</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/contact">Start a platform discussion</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
